核心能力 Competence
■ 培養「整合設計」、「策略設計企劃」、「程序設計」以及「通用設計」等專業能力。
 Cultivate “Integral design”, “Strategy design planning”, “Programming”, “Universal design” ability.
□ 培養學生具有以人類行為之角度去探討產品、介面與互動等相關研究之能力
 Cultivate students to use human behavior point of view to discuss products, interface, and interaction.
□ 培養學生運用電腦輔助設計及其相關理論之能力
 Cultivate students to use computer aided design and relative theories.
□ 培養感性工學理論之研究能力
 Cultivate research ability of sensitive engineering theories.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       This subject describes the research and application of Kansei Engineering in various merchandises. The categories of Kansei merchandises, will be discussed, include tangible products, intangible services, business procedure, marketing, information, interaction, experiences, environment, etc. It will intend to discover emotional design that ranges from a fundamental level, such as graphics, to a superior level, such as a customer’ shopping experience. In design, the purpose of Kasei Engineering has been evolving from creating aesthetic form to evoking pleasant emotion in interaction/use. This subject contributes to explore the possibilities and varieties of emotional design.

Students will be working on a series of literature review, case studies, research proposal, and, finally, paper writing. The final paper will be encouraged to be published in any international conference. After this course, students will better understand the future trend of Kansei design and familiarize themselves with the research in Kansei.

The course will cover:
-The meaning and power of Kansei design in the future. The types of Kansei design that satisfy users’ needs or dominate their preferences when shopping.
-The new perspectives, methods, or tools of Kansei design applied to products, services, business, marketing, information, interaction, experience, environment, etc.
-The exercise of literature review, including the selection of quality papers, the review techniques, and the knowledge a quality paper elicits.
-The development of a secondary research, involving the process of conducting an elementary but critical discussion and the principle of writing a clear paper.

Complementing the above will:
-Develop each student’s understanding in Kansei research
-Strengthen each student’s assessment capability in Kansei design 
-Make each student become a design thinker in addition to a design practitioner
-Grow each student’s international publications
